Steps below shows process of creating a kubernetes cluster using KOPS and then deploying wordpress to the cluster.

1. Launch EC2 with custom role to run KOPS using CloudFormation template below.

AWSTemplateFormatVersion: 2010-09-09
Description: >
  Template will create role with necessary permissions to run kops on EC2.
Parameters:
  AZ:
    Description: Select availability zone to launch in
    Type: AWS::EC2::AvailabilityZone::Name
Resources:
  KopsRole:
    Type: AWS::IAM::Role
    Properties:
      AssumeRolePolicyDocument: 
        Version: "2012-10-17"
        Statement: 
          - Effect: "Allow"
            Principal: 
              Service: 
                - "ec2.amazonaws.com"
            Action: 
              - "sts:AssumeRole"
      Path: "/"
      ManagedPolicyArns:
        - arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonEC2FullAccess
        - arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/IAMFullAccess
        - arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonS3FullAccess
        - arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonVPCFullAccess
        - arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonRoute53FullAccess
        - arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonSSMManagedInstanceCore
  KopsInstanceProfile:
    Type: AWS::IAM::InstanceProfile
    Properties:
      Path: "/"
      Roles:
      - !Ref KopsRole
  ec2:
    Type: AWS::EC2::Instance
    Properties:
      ImageId: "ami-0e691f7684990f408" # AMI prebaked with packages and dependancies
      KeyName: "default" 
      InstanceType: "t2.micro"
      IamInstanceProfile: !Ref KopsInstanceProfile
      SecurityGroups:
        - "SSHSecurityGroup" 
      AvailabilityZone: !Ref AZ
      Tags:
        - Key: "Name"
          Value: "kops"

2. SSH into instance and use KOPS to deploy a 2 node cluster.

3. Validate cluster, verify nodes are up and running, get yaml files and deploy wordpress

from IPython.display import HTML
import base64
import io

def play(myvideo):
    video = io.open(myvideo, 'r+b').read()
    encoded = base64.b64encode(video)
    return(HTML(data='''<video width="960" height="540" controls>
    <source src="data:video/mp4;base64,{0}" type="video/mp4" /></video>'''.format(encoded.decode('ascii'))))
